# ansible-lint BASELINE — grandfathered existing violations (file + rule).
#
# These are pre-existing shell/correctness findings in live-verified playbooks,
# mostly the intentional remote-over-SSH pattern (podman/oc/tar/aliyun through
# `{{ _ssh_root_mirror }}` on non-managed hosts) where risky-shell-pipe /
# no-changed-when / command-instead-of-* can't be cleanly resolved. They are
# ignored so the gate is GREEN today; the point of the gate is to stop NEW
# violations in NEW files, not to force a churn of working code.
#
# Matching is per (file, rule) — a new violation of one of these rules in a file
# NOT listed here fails CI. To (re)generate after a deliberate cleanup:
#   ansible-lint --generate-ignore ansible/
#   # then drop the cosmetic buckets (name*/yaml*/jinja*/var-naming*) — those are
#   # demoted to warnings in .ansible-lint, not baselined.
#
# Cosmetic rules (yaml formatting, task naming, jinja spacing) are NOT here — see
# warn_list in .ansible-lint. Burn this list down over time; don't grow it.
